quran[8]{c,v,t}:
  102,1,"Vying for more distracted youpl"
  102,2,"until you visited the graves."
  102,3,"But no! Youpl will come to know."
  102,4,"Once again: But no! Youpl will come to know."
  102,5,"But no! If only youpl knew with the knowledge of certitude:"
  102,6,"you will certainly see purgatory.",footnotes:366529:1
  102,7,"Then youpl will certainly see it with the eye of certitude."
  102,8,"Then, on that day, youpl will certainly be asked about (worldly) bliss."
